beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob:
This is my go to Hef when I'm out of Homebrew. I would rate it higher but I'm not a big fan of leaving a lot of yeast in my beer. I always double rack my Hefs and they are as flavorful as this Hef with half the yeast. Overall, it's a great Hef.....just don't move it around to much before you poor and leave the yeast in the bottle!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

One of my favorites but way to expensive. I buy it at Costco, (3) 750ml for 19.99. I've had some batches that taste better than others. I've even had to take a few bottles back in certain batches that were really bad. But overall, most of the bottles I have had were excellent.
